A vintage-style technical blueprint illustration showing an intricate mechanical contraption where multiple brass gears, pulleys, and pneumatic tubes connect different ornate Victorian-era machines. Each machine has unique gauges, dials, and spinning components, all working in harmony through visible connection points. The scene depicts the concept of interconnected systems communicating through standardized interfaces, rendered in sepia tones with cream paper texture, detailed cross-hatching, and subtle copper and bronze metallic accents. Steam wisps curl between the mechanisms, and delicate measurement rulers frame the edges of the composition. The perspective is isometric, showing the elegant complexity of the integrated system from above at an angle.
